### ✅ **Java Static Block (Initialization Block)**

A **static block** in Java is used to **initialize static variables**.
It is executed **only once** when the class is **first loaded into memory**, *before* the `main()` method runs.

---

### 🧪 Simple Example:

```java
public class StaticBlockDemo {
    static int number;

    // Static block
    static {
        number = 50;
        System.out.println("Static block executed. Number set to: " + number);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Main method started. Number is: " + number);
    }
}
```

---

### 🔍 Output:

```
Static block executed. Number set to: 50
Main method started. Number is: 50
```

---

### 🧠 Hinglish Explanation:

> Jab Java class memory mein load hoti hai, tab static block **sirf ek baar** run hota hai.
> Ye mainly **static variables ko initialize karne** ke liye use hota hai.
> `main()` se pehle chalta hai — jise aap ek baar ka setup samajh sakte ho.

---
